3. Once upon a time, in a small village, there lived three little pigs and a little girl named Little Red Riding Hood. The three little pigs decided to build their own houses. The first little pig built his house out of straw, the second little pig built his house out of sticks, and the third little pig built his house out of bricks.

One day, Little Red Riding Hood was walking through the forest to visit her grandmother. She met the three little pigs on her way. The first little pig invited her to his straw house, but she politely declined, knowing it wouldn't be safe. The second little pig invited her to his stick house, but she also declined for the same reason. The third little pig, however, invited her to his sturdy brick house, and she accepted.

As they were enjoying their time together, the Big Bad Wolf appeared. He huffed and puffed and blew down the straw house and the stick house, but he couldn't blow down the brick house. The three little pigs and Little Red Riding Hood were safe inside.

The wolf, frustrated, tried to trick Little Red Riding Hood by disguising himself as her grandmother. However, Little Red Riding Hood was clever and noticed the wolf's true identity. She quickly warned the three little pigs, and together, they outsmarted the wolf.

In the end, the three little pigs and Little Red Riding Hood lived happily and safely in the brick house, knowing the importance of hard work and good choices. [end of text]


